This paper deals with list decoding in the Levenshtein metric, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses upper and lower bounds on list decoding, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents an efficient list decoding algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
